  "text": "A multilayer perceptron (MLP) comprises numerous layers. This type of architecture propagates feature data in a feed-forward way through the layers, and it can be calibrated in a way that minimizes the quadratic error [CITATION_1] . In literature, there are many references of MLP applications for weed and crop management cases.",
